{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b844312-06f2-4a64-8886-252e999563d7","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use the modern constructor-injection pattern:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via constructor (no more static property).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` (supports `async Task`).\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private readonly MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Constructor injection of `TestContext` replaced the old `public static TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` pattern.\n- `[TestInitialize]` runs before each test and supports `async Task`.\n- For **class-level** async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` (static, also supports `async Task`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f34d884-e6d1-46ed-b8eb-fc85110b6402","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) rather than the old static property pattern.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor for sync initialization.\n3. **Async init**: Implement `IAsyncInitialization` — wait, that's not MSTest. In MSTest, you use `[TestInitialize]` for per-test init (which supports async). For class-level, use `[ClassInitialize]` (static).\n\n\n4. **Async support**: Both `[TestInitialize]` and `[ClassInitialize]` can be async in v3, accepting `async Task` return types.\n\nThe cleanest pattern is injecting `TestContext` through the constructor and using `[TestInitialize]` for any async setup work.","outputTokens":668,"requestId":"340A:3A1698:B074FC:CF4434:69F4036F"},"id":"86a661e4-0412-4a93-9bad-fc4ff72888b8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:35:57.426Z","parentId":"4ec53ede-8d42-4dc5-8159-b575b3c2a751"}
